public struct CacheConfig

CacheConfig struct is used for providing the caching configurations necessary for the HTTP caching client.

Field Name Data Type Description Default Value
enabled boolean Specifies whether HTTP caching is enabled. Caching is enabled by default.
isShared boolean Specifies whether the HTTP caching client should behave as a public cache or a private cache
expiryTimeMillis int The number of milliseconds to keep an entry in the cache
capacity int The capacity of the cache
evictionFactor float The fraction of entries to be removed when the cache is full. The value should be between 0 (exclusive) and 1 (inclusive).
policy CachingPolicy Gives the user some control over the caching behaviour. By default, this is set to CACHE_CONTROL_AND_VALIDATORS. The default behaviour is to allow caching only when the Cache-Control header and either the ETag or Last-Modified header are present.

  • < CacheConfig > CacheConfig()

    Initializes the CacheConfig struct to its default values

  • < CacheConfig > CacheConfig.<init>()

public struct ClientEndpointConfiguration

ClientEndpointConfiguration struct represents options to be used for HTTP client invocation

Field Name Data Type Description Default Value
circuitBreaker CircuitBreakerConfig | null Circuit Breaker configuration
endpointTimeout int Endpoint timeout value in millisecond
keepAlive boolean Specifies whether to reuse a connection for multiple requests
transferEncoding TransferEncoding The types of encoding applied to the request
chunking Chunking The chunking behaviour of the request
httpVersion string The HTTP version understood by the client
forwarded string The choice of setting forwarded/x-forwarded header
followRedirects FollowRedirects | null Redirect related options
retry Retry | null Retry related options
proxy Proxy | null Proxy server related options
connectionThrottling ConnectionThrottling | null Configurations for connection throttling
targets TargetService[] Service(s) accessible through the endpoint. Multiple services can be specified here when using techniques such as load balancing and fail over. []
lbMode string | FailoverConfig circuitBreaker: Circuit Breaker configuration
cacheConfig CacheConfig HTTP caching related configurations []
acceptEncoding string Specifies the way of handling accept-encoding header.

  • < ClientEndpointConfiguration > ClientEndpointConfiguration()

    Initializes the ClientEndpointConfiguration struct with default values.

  • < ClientEndpointConfiguration > ClientEndpointConfiguration.<init>()

public annotation WebSocketServiceConfig

Configurations annotation for a WebSocket service

NO_CACHE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
NO_CACHE string Forces the cache to validate a cached response with the origin server before serving.

NO_STORE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
NO_STORE string Instructs the cache to not store a response in non-volatile storage.

NO_TRANSFORM

Attribute Name Data Type Description
NO_TRANSFORM string Instructs intermediaries not to transform the payload.

MAX_AGE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
MAX_AGE string When used in requests, it implies that clients are not willing to accept responses whose age is greater than max-age. When used in responses, the response is to be considered stale after the specified number of seconds.

MAX_STALE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
MAX_STALE string Indicates that the client is willing to accept responses which have exceeded their freshness lifetime by no more than the specified number of seconds.

MIN_FRESH

Attribute Name Data Type Description
MIN_FRESH string Indicates that the client is only accepting responses whose freshness lifetime >= current age + min-fresh

ONLY_IF_CACHED

Attribute Name Data Type Description
ONLY_IF_CACHED string Indicates that the client is only willing to accept a cached response. A cached response is served subject to other constraints posed by the request.

MUST_REVALIDATE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
MUST_REVALIDATE string Indicates that once the response has become stale, it should not be reused for subsequent requests without validating with the origin server.

PUBLIC

Attribute Name Data Type Description
PUBLIC string Indicates that any cache may store the response.

PRIVATE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
PRIVATE string Indicates that the response is intended for a single user and should not be stored by shared caches.

PROXY_REVALIDATE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
PROXY_REVALIDATE string Has the same meaning as must-revalidate, except that this does not apply to private caches.

S_MAX_AGE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
S_MAX_AGE string In shared caches, this overrides the max-age or Expires header field

MAX_STALE_ANY_AGE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
MAX_STALE_ANY_AGE int A constant for indicating that the max-stale directive does not specify a limit.

IF_MATCH

IF_MODIFIED_SINCE

Attribute Name Data Type Description
IF_MODIFIED_SINCE string HTTP header key 'if-modified-since'. Used when validating (with the origin server) whether a cached response is still valid. If the representation of the resource has modified since the timestamp in this field, a 304 response is returned.

IF_NONE_MATCH

Attribute Name Data Type Description
IF_NONE_MATCH string HTTP header key 'if-none-match'. Used when validating (with the origin server) whether a cached response is still valid. If the ETag provided in this field matches the representation of the requested resource, a 304 response is returned.

IF_RANGE
